.TH man 3 "29 Octuber 2022" "VIM-8.1" "_printf man page"

.SH NAME
_printf
- re-creation of the printf function

.SH SYNOPSIS
#include "main.h"

int _printf(const char *format, ...);

.SH DESCRIPTION
The _printf() function sends a formatted string to the standard output(the display). Format specifications, beginning with a percent sign (%)
If do you wan to print a character
%c: to be used to print character

%d: to be used to print decimal(integer)number(base 10)

%i: integer(base 10)

%s: a string of characters

.SH RETURN VALUE
It returns the number of characters that are printed. If there is some error then it returns a negative value.
